Blast in train kills 3 in Pakistan
At least three persons were killed and 15 others injured today when a blast hit a passenger train, derailing its seven coaches in central Pakistan. The blast derailed coaches of the Khushhal Khan Khattak Express train, two of which were overturned, according to Chief Controller Railway Station Naseem Ahmed Doger.
The train was reportedly travelling at 60-70km per hour from Peshawar to Karachiwhen the explosion occurred.
General Manager of PakistanRailwayssaid the oil tank of the train was also damaged due to the explosion.
A large crater has formed under the track, making rescue efforts difficult.